    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="822"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d822">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/15245</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Deputy Director of the
                        Office of Far Eastern Affairs</hi> (<hi rend="italic"
                    >Ballantine</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-17">January 17,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <table>
                    <row>
                        <cell rendition="#nowrap #top">Participants:</cell>
                        <cell rendition="#hanging">Mr. Liu Chieh, Chargé d’Affaires ad interim,
                            Chinese Embassy</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell rendition="#hanging">Mr. Stanley K. Hornbeck<note n="6"
                                xml:id="d822fn6">Director of the Office of Far Eastern
                                Affairs.</note>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell rendition="#hanging">Mr. Joseph W. Ballantine</cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <p>Mr. Liu called at our request. We made representations in regard to an attack by
                    armed Chinese on an American military convoy near Kunming, as reported by the
                    Embassy at Chungking, along lines in the attached copy of an oral statement<note
                        n="7" xml:id="d822fn7">
                        <hi rend="italic">Infra</hi>.</note> which we handed him as a record of our
                    oral representations. Mr. Liu expressed himself as, being impressed by the
                    seriousness of the matter and said that he-would not fail to take the matter up
                    with his Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J[<hi rend="smallcaps">oseph</hi>] W. B[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >allantine</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
